<div class="faq-container">
  <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>1. How do I upload notes?</h3>
    <p>You must be logged in and have a verified account. Go to <a href="/upload">Upload Notes</a>, fill in details like title, subject, semester, course, and upload a PDF file (max 15MB).</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>2. Why do I need verification?</h3>
    <p>Verification ensures that only genuine SVVV students contribute. You can verify by submitting your Student ID document at <a href="/verify">Verify Account</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>3. How can I explore available notes?</h3>
    <p>Visit <a href="/explore">Explore</a> to browse all verified notes. You can search, filter by course, semester etc.</p>
  </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>4. What file formats can I upload?</h3>
        <p>Currently, only PDF files are supported (maximum size 15MB).</p>
    </div>



  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>5. What is the Contributor Leaderboard?</h3>
    <p>Our <a href="/rankings">Contributor Leaderboard</a> highlights the top users who uploaded the most notes.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>6. Can I request notes I donâ€™t find?</h3>
    <p>Yes! Go to <a href="/requestnotes">Request Notes</a> and post your request. Other users may upload it.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>7. I forgot my password. What should I do?</h3>
    <p>Go to <a href="/forgot">Forgot Password</a>. You will receive an OTP on your registered email to reset your password.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>8. Can I edit or delete my notes?</h3>
    <p>Yes, go to the note page and click edit or delete (only available if you are the owner or a moderator).</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>9. How do I update my profile?</h3>
    <p>You can edit your profile details or upload a new avatar from your <a href="/profile/<%= currUser?._id %>">profile page</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>10. Who manages verifications and notes?</h3>
    <p>Our moderator and admin team review user verification requests and uploaded notes to maintain quality and authenticity.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>4. How does voting work?</h3>
    <p>Each user can upvote notes they find helpful. Notes with the most upvotes appear in <a href="/most-voted">Most Voted</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>12. Can I upload notes without logging in?</h3>
    <p>No, you must log in and verify your account before uploading notes.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>13. What happens if my note gets rejected?</h3>
    <p>If moderators find issues (irrelevant, spam, or low quality), the note may be rejected. You can improve it and re-upload.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>14. Are downloads free?</h3>
    <p>Yes, downloading notes and all the available activites on CampusNotes is completely free for all users.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>15. Can I delete my account?</h3>
    <p>Currently, you can edit your profile. For account deletion, please contact our support team.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>16. How do I report inappropriate content?</h3>
    <p>Use the <a href="/feedback">Feedback</a> page or contact us via email/Discord to report any inappropriate content.</p>
  </div>
